<holidayType guid="7b3f8dd1-c1a3-4cff-b909-6f65982d8c18" id="24078" nodeName="Free Half Day Wine Tour" isDoc="" updated="2022-05-25T13:33:20.8100000Z" parentGUID="e65cbae5-17c8-4dcc-a98e-cbd6e7154c59" nodeTypeAlias="holidayType" templateAlias="HolidayType" sortOrder="18" published="false" isBlueprint="false">
  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow"><img src="/media/13049203/wine-shot.jpg" alt="Free Half Day Wine Tour" rel="858,410" /></div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>Book a 7 night or longer <strong><a data-udi="umb://document/96a3e4d143704d3e93793368e4fc0416" href="/{localLink:umb://document/96a3e4d143704d3e93793368e4fc0416}" title="Lakes &amp; Mountains Holidays">Lakes and Mountains</a></strong> holiday to <strong>Lake Garda</strong> this summer, and receive a FREE half day wine tour worth £74 per couple.</p>
<p>Vineyards are plentiful in the regions of <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda"><strong>Lake Garda</strong></a> with a wide range of choice from the different varieties of grapes grown here. The <strong>Trentino</strong> wines, benefitting from the micro climate include white wines such as Chardonnay, Pinot Grigio, and Sauvignon. From Bardolino the Classico is one of the best known wines but there is a rose “Chiaretto” made from the first pressing of the Barbera grape.<br /> <br />Our half day wine tour provides a thoroughly pleasant afternoon spent visiting one of the region’s many renowned wine producers. A tour through their vineyard and the cellars to learn the techniques of wine making and to finish, enjoy tasting a selection of wines. A must if you like Italian wine.</p>
<p>Guests staying in <a data-udi="umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c}" title="Limone"><strong>Limone</strong></a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva"><strong>Riva</strong></a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce" href="/{localLink:umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce}" title="Malcesine"><strong>Malcesine</strong></a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/689f022eb7974a7087ccbecf4adbda43" href="/{localLink:umb://document/689f022eb7974a7087ccbecf4adbda43}" title="Garda"><strong>Garda</strong></a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1}" title="Bardolino"><strong>Bardolino</strong></a> will venture east of <strong>Lake Garda</strong> to visit the beautiful wine region of <strong>Valpolicella</strong> in the province of <a data-udi="umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b}" title="Verona"><strong>Verona</strong></a>, and enjoy 4-5 wine tastings at the <strong>Tenute Ugolini</strong> vineyard.<br /> <br />Guests staying in <a data-udi="umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11}" title="Gardone Riviera"><strong>Gardone</strong></a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/93a0ea3cd0334ca088eaf788bad0faba" href="/{localLink:umb://document/93a0ea3cd0334ca088eaf788bad0faba}" title="Sirmione"><strong>Sirmione</strong></a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b}" title="Desenzano"><strong>Desenzano</strong></a> will travel south of <strong>Lake Garda</strong> to explore <strong>Cantina Colli Morenici</strong> for 3 wine tastings before discovering the quaint village of <strong>Borghetto</strong> near to the vineyard. A perfect opportunity to take some photos of this pretty Italian scenery.<br /> <br />Guests staying in <a data-udi="umb://document/0f9f33f516a448a2ab8bda68f2fba594" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0f9f33f516a448a2ab8bda68f2fba594}" title="Peschiera"><strong>Peschiera</strong></a> are able to choose from either the <strong>Valpolicella</strong> or the <strong>Cantina Colli Morenici</strong> tour.</p>
<p> </p>
